  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> When I talk about Refinement, I can only relate to RefinementList(dFR) and Menu(fR).\n\nYep, still, ultimately all connectors are doing refinements, in a way or another (numeric, faceting, sort). And I would rather not have the user to learn all the different APIS those connectors expose.\n\n> Even if we keep the same name, there is a confusion in the way it accepts the props.\n\nYes and that will be the only thing you need to know, not the parameter or method naming.\n\n> Also I would be pretty confused if hitsPerPage is renamed to default or current Refinement.\n\nI hesitated on this one indeed. If you come from a previous Algolia experience with instantsearch.js it will be seen as weird. If you are new to Algolia and only learning the connectors API, this should be a consistent experience with all the other connectors.\n",
    "created_at": "2016-10-17T10:00:00Z",
